longBusinessSummary: Crystal Lake Mining Corporation engages in the identification, acquisition, and exploration of precious metal resources in Canada. The company holds 100% interest in the Tom Cat Property covering an area of approximately 687 hectares located in British Columbia. It also has an option to acquire a 100% interest in the Newmont Lake Project that consists of 638 square kilometers of mineral claims located in the Eskay region in the Northwest of Golden Triangle. The company was formerly known as Sierra Iron Ore Corporation and changed its name to Crystal Lake Mining Corporation in July 2016. Crystal Lake Mining Corporation was incorporated in 2009 and is headquartered in Kelowna, Canada.
